contentrichtext.text: {{BLP sources|date=June 2009}} '''Julie Aberg Robison''' (born November 30, 1958) is a member of the town council of [[Cary, North Carolina]]. Born in [[Madison, Wisconsin]], Robison holds a master's degree in urban and regional planning from the [[University of Wisconsinâ€“Madison]]. A public administration specialist with [[Research Triangle Institute]], Robison has lived in Cary since 1997, was first elected to the Cary Town Council in 2001 as an at-large representative, and re-elected to that position in 2005 and 2007. Although her office is officially non-partisan, Robison is affiliated with the [[United States Democratic Party|Democratic Party]]. She was elected as mayor pro-tem<ref name="Wise">{{cite news|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/2009/12/09/232107/forum-tackles-falls-lake.html|title=Forum tackles Falls Lake|last=Wise|first=Jim|date=8 December 2009|work=News Observer|accessdate=23 March 2011}}</ref> in December 2007.
